cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed stream processing frameworks and scheduling algorithms for maximizing throughput in a heterogeneous cluster.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses a design and implementation of a scheduling algorithm that optimizes resource utilization and throughput.
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed scheduling algorithm and compares it to the default scheduler of Storm.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with stream processing and data transmission over a network.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the design and implementation of a scheduling algorithm for optimizing the processing of a directed acyclic graph.
